3355	  \textit{Quasi-coherence data gives a presentation on each cover member's pullback.}
3356	  Let \(M\) be a sheaf of modules on \(X\), let \(q\) be quasi-coherence data for
3357	  \(M\), and let \(i\) be a cover index. There is a presentation of the geometric
3358	  pullback of \(M\) to the open subscheme \(q.X_i\):
3359	  \[
3360	    \bigl((q.X_i).\iota^{*}\,M\bigr).\mathrm{Presentation} .
3361	  \]
3362	\end{definition}
3363	\begin{proof}
3364	  \uses{def:over_restrict_presentation, lem:quasicoherentData_bind_mathlib}
3365	  The datum \(q\) packages, for each index \(i\), a slice presentation
3366	  \(q.\mathrm{presentation}\,i : (M.\mathrm{over}\,(q.X_i)).\mathrm{Presentation}\)
3367	  over the cover member \(q.X_i\) (the per-member presentations whose binding is
3368	  recorded by \(\mathrm{QuasicoherentData}\), \cref{lem:quasicoherentData_bind_mathlib}).
3369	  Feeding this slice presentation to \cref{def:over_restrict_presentation} at
3370	  \(U = q.X_i\) produces the desired presentation of the geometric pullback
3371	  \((q.X_i).\iota^{*}\,M\).
3372	\end{proof}
